The ISO codes dependency is a problem you need to solve differently.
The plugin uses sokil/php-isocodes to convert a WooCommerce billing country alpha-2 code (e.g. "CV") to its ISO 3166-1 numeric code ("132" for Cape Verde). In a Worker, you have no Composer. You need to solve this in one of two ways:
Option A - Hardcode the common cases, fall back to a lookup table. For a Cape Verde merchant, 95%+ of transactions will be CV -> 132. Build a small hardcoded map for the countries your customers actually come from:
